SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 91
BY SENATOR BOUDREAUX
COMMENDATIONS. Commends and congratulates Progressive Baptist Church on the
occasion of its one hundredth anniversary.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend and congratulate Progressive Baptist Church of Lafayette, Louisiana, upon the
3 celebration of its one hundredth anniversary and to recognize the church's century
4 of faith, service, and spiritual leadership in the community.
5 WHEREAS, in 1925, Progressive Baptist Church was founded by Brothers and
6 Sisters Warren Hall, W. O. Brian, R. Andersen, and Henry Sias and has served as a steadfast
7 beacon of faith, hope, and community service since that time; and
8 WHEREAS, shortly after its organization, Reverend A. C. Marshall was called to
9 serve as the first pastor of the new church, leading a dedicated congregation of nine
10 members; and
11 WHEREAS, the small, white frame church was built in 1926, marking a new era of
12 growth and stability for the congregation, and became affiliated with the Seventh District
13 Missionary Baptist Association; and
14 WHEREAS, Reverend Marshall faithfully served Progressive Baptist Church for
15 twenty years, after which Reverend Alex, Reverend J. J. Webster, Reverend E. D. Rideaux,
16 Reverend C. R. Steward, and Reverend Freddie Banks were each called in turn to serve as
17 pastors, continuing the church's mission of spreading the gospel and strengthening its
18 ministry; and
