1 WHEREAS, Reverend Raymond Smith later became pastor and oversaw a period
2 of remarkable growth and development, including the expansion and renovation of the
3 church building in 1953, to accommodate the increasing membership and the purchase of
4 property for future expansion and construction, ultimately building the Fellowship Hall and
5 securing land for use as a church cemetery; and
6 WHEREAS, following Reverend Smith's pastorship, Pastor Lloyd Joiner Jr. was
7 called to serve as pastor of Progressive Baptist Church, ushering in an extraordinary era of
8 growth, vision, and ministry; and
9 WHEREAS, under Pastor Joiner's dynamic leadership, the current sanctuary was
10 constructed, and the church continued to expand with numerous renovations and
11 improvements, including construction of the Lloyd Joiner Jr. Educational Building to
12 provide space for Christian education and ministries, as well as a daycare facility adjacent
13 to the building to serve the needs of families in the community; and
14 WHEREAS, Pastor Joiner's commitment to community engagement also led to the
15 establishment of the Progressive Community Outreach Center, which serves both the
16 congregation and the wider Lafayette community by hosting health screenings, a GED
17 program, sports events, financial literacy classes, grief share meetings, a summer enrichment
18 program, and a testing center – all with the mission of sharing the love and word of God; and
19 WHEREAS, under Pastor Joiner's continued vision, the United Theological Seminary
20 and Bible College established an extension campus on the grounds of Progressive Baptist
21 Church, training men and women of various Christian denominations for leadership within
22 their churches, communities, and beyond; and
23 WHEREAS, after forty-four years of faithful service, Pastor Lloyd Joiner, Jr. retired
24 and now serves honorably as Pastor Emeritus; and
25 WHEREAS, on October 15, 2023, Dr. Chad E. Nora was elected as the next pastor
26 of Progressive Baptist Church and since assuming leadership, he has emphasized three core
27 focuses: strong biblical teaching, a loving and sincere church community, and caring,
28 effective, and meaningful outreach; and
29 WHEREAS, Pastor Chad has overseen multiple facility upgrades, modernized church
30 operations through digital innovation, introduced new ministry initiatives, and established
